                <fr:title text="Morphisms between affine schemes are quasi-separated">Morphisms between affine schemes are quasi-separated</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
  Morphisms between affine schemes are <fr:link href="/schm-0B23/" title="Quasi-separated and separated morphisms" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-0B23/" display-uri="schm-0B23" type="local">quasi-separated</fr:link>, since their diagonals will again be morphisms between affine schemes, and all such morphisms are quasi-compact by <fr:link href="/schm-WGUQ/" title="Affine morphisms are quasi-compact" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-WGUQ/" display-uri="schm-WGUQ" type="local">Example <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-WGUQ/" display-uri="schm-WGUQ" /></fr:link>. However, unlike the case in algebraic geometry, not all maps between affine schemes are <fr:link href="/schm-0B23/" title="Quasi-separated and separated morphisms" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-0B23/" display-uri="schm-0B23" type="local">separated</fr:link>.
</html:p>
