            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors />
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>6</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>18</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://charloced.github.io/schm-C8GC/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>schm-C8GC</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/schm-C8GC/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Separated and non-separated maps between affine schemes">Separated and non-separated maps between affine schemes</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
  Here we discuss some examples of separated and non-separated affine schemes. For a positive example, consider the following map between finite affine schemes,
  
  <html:figure><fr:resource hash="953c60d335fe7e72bfd13b8501e0c752"><fr:resource-content><html:img src="/953c60d335fe7e72bfd13b8501e0c752.svg" /></fr:resource-content><fr:resource-source type="latex" part="preamble"><![CDATA[\usepackage {tikz-cd}\usepackage {quiver}]]></fr:resource-source><fr:resource-source type="latex" part="body"><![CDATA[
    \begin {tikzcd}
      \bullet  && \bullet  & \bullet  \\
      & \bullet  && \bullet 
      \arrow [curve={height=-18pt}, dashed, from=1-1, to=1-4]
      \arrow [dashed, from=1-3, to=1-4]
      \arrow [from=2-2, to=1-1]
      \arrow [from=2-2, to=1-3]
      \arrow [dashed, from=2-2, to=2-4]
      \arrow [from=2-4, to=1-4]
    \end {tikzcd}
  ]]></fr:resource-source></fr:resource></html:figure>

  which corresponds to the distributive lattice morphism
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ x \mapsto  y \vee  z : 2[x] \to  y \wedge  z/2[y,z] ]]></fr:tex>
  By the characterisation in <fr:link href="/schm-FHDX/" title="Separated morphisms between affine schemes" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-FHDX/" display-uri="schm-FHDX" type="local">Proposition <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-FHDX/" display-uri="schm-FHDX" /></fr:link>, this map is <fr:link href="/schm-0B23/" title="Quasi-separated and separated morphisms" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-0B23/" display-uri="schm-0B23" type="local">separated</fr:link>.
</html:p>
                <html:p>
