            <fr:title text="Quasi-separated and separated morphisms">Quasi-separated and separated morphisms</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  A map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : X \to  Y]]></fr:tex> between <fr:link href="/schm-86OJ/" title="Scheme" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-86OJ/" display-uri="schm-86OJ" type="local">schemes</fr:link> is <html:em>(quasi-)separated</html:em>, if the diagonal <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Delta  : X \to  X \times _Y X]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/schm-FH0V/" title="Closed immersion" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-FH0V/" display-uri="schm-FH0V" type="local">closed immersion</fr:link> (<fr:link href="/schm-BH0E/" title="Quasi-compact morphisms" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-BH0E/" display-uri="schm-BH0E" type="local">quasi-compact</fr:link>).
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
